channel.title: My ip is 0.0.0.0? WTF!?!?!
channel.description: When i run a server for example pimpscape is say "Starting Pimpscape on ip 0.0.0.0" And i want it to "Starting Pimpscape on sckumscape.no-ip.biz PLZ HELP!

item.title: My ip is 0.0.0.0? WTF!?!?!
item.dc:creator: @akl akl
item.description:
@akl wrote:

[quote="(Anthony), post:23, topic:221699"][quote author=eaglith link=topic=291107.msg2347251#msg2347251 date=1216790819]

Your IP is not 0.0.0.0, it just prints that you idiot. Servers don’t ‘start’ on IP addresses, they bind to ports on some or all network adapters, and any connections routed to them are handled by them. So you screwed up port forwarding.

Oh no you actually tried to tech someone something you deserve a ban.

When i run a server for example pimpscape is say “Starting Pimpscape on ip 0.0.0.0” And i want it to "Starting Pimpscape on sckumscape.no-ip.biz PLZ HELP!

Please learn how the internet works.
You are hosting from localhost, eg the 0.0.0.0
So the server is running on your computer.
0.0.0.0 is what it would be to get on your server from your computer.

Jesus don’t be so hard on him, both of you. He was asking about a simple problem, thats what this forum section is for. If you’re going to flame you might want to try a fan site, not an informative site.
[/quote]
I answered it dumbfuck,
get a brain[/quote]
This site is far from informative. Why not drop by sometime when talk science, eh?
‘Jesus’ - one word you wouldn’t wanna use here.
